Package: batchman
Title: A wrapper for R methods to run them in arbitrary batches
Version: 1.3.0.9006
Author: Peter Hurford <peter@peterhurford.com>
Maintainer: Peter Hurford <peter@peterhurford.com>
Authors@R: person("Peter", "Hurford", email = "peter@peterhurford.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Batchman is a wrapper for R methods to run them in arbitary
    batches. Some methods crash when running on large inputs.  Batchman helps
    prevent those crashes, and helps increase speed where batching is useful.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.0.1)
Imports:
    methods,
    checkr
Suggests:
    R6,
    plyr,
    parallel,
    testthat,
    knitr,
    microbenchmark,
    progress,
Remotes: robertzk/rocco,
    gaborcsardi/progress,
    peterhurford/checkr
